{"DAW":[{"def":"A European bird of the Crow family (Corvus monedula), often nesting in church towers and ruins; a jackdaw.","pos":""}],"DAWDLE":[{"def":"To waste time in trifling employment; to trifle; to saunter.","pos":""}],"DAWDLER":[{"def":"One who wastes time in trifling employments; an idler; a trifler.","pos":""}],"DAWK":[{"def":"To cut or mark with an incision; to gash.","pos":""}],"DAWN":[{"def":"To begin to grow light in the morning; to grow light; to break, or begin to appear; as, the day dawns; the morning dawns.","pos":""},{"def":"To began to give promise; to begin to appear or to expand.","pos":""}],"DAWSONITE":[{"def":"A hydrous carbonate of alumina and soda, occuring in white, bladed crustals.","pos":""}]}